00:01:41.180 --> 00:01:46.360
and it's adductor longus and, well, as you
can imagine, longus means long. And so it's

00:01:46.360 --> 00:01:51.320
longer than brevis and of course magnus is
really huge compared to all of them. So we

00:01:51.320 --> 00:01:56.100
have three different abductor muscles all
very close to one another. And so how do you

00:01:56.100 --> 00:02:01.180
tell them apart? Well, their names! One is
very big, one is short, and one is long. Now

00:02:01.180 --> 00:02:05.741
one weird thing about Latin, you probably
already noticed, is the words seem to the

00:02:05.741 --> 00:02:10.590
words seem to be backwards in the phrase.
Let's take a closer look at that. In English,

00:02:10.590 --> 00:02:17.620
when we have a phrase like red wagon, in Latin
it would be rendered as wagon red instead,

00:02:17.620 --> 00:02:22.150
of course using Latin words, not English words.
But this is to show the word order. So there

00:02:22.150 --> 00:02:27.939
is a different word order these two languages.
And so the modifier, which is the adjective,

00:02:27.939 --> 00:02:35.900
in this case red, is modifying a noun. Which
in this case is wagon. And so the modifier

00:02:35.900 --> 00:02:41.150
comes after the term that it modifies in Latin,
which is backwards from English. Let's look

00:02:41.150 --> 00:02:48.080
at another example. Big red wagon. In Latin,
that would be rendered as wagon red big. And

00:02:48.080 --> 00:02:53.980
so the modifiers come after the terms being
modified. So let's apply that to one of these

00:02:53.980 --> 00:03:01.799
Latin names like, ooh, here's a long one:
extensor carpi radialis brevis. That sounds

00:03:01.799 --> 00:03:07.319
like a mouthful but it's really kind of a
whole phrase or sentence in Latin. An extensor,

00:03:07.319 --> 00:03:14.879
of course, is going to extend a part, that
is, stretch it out. And carpi means of the

00:03:14.879 --> 00:03:20.199
wrist. Remember carpal bones, or the wrist
bones. Radialis in this case means pertaining

00:03:20.199 --> 00:03:25.909
to, or near, or at the radius bone of the
forearm. And then brevis, we already know,

00:03:25.909 --> 00:03:30.590
means short. So if we put that all together
and translate it into a good English word

00:03:30.590 --> 00:03:36.760
order, it means the short wrist stretcher
at the radius. Which tells you an awful lot

00:03:36.760 --> 00:03:44.409
about that muscle: where to find it and what
is does. Now there are some other names of

00:03:44.409 --> 00:03:50.349
